The Zamfara State Police Command has asked indigenes who participated in the last Physical and Credential screening exercise to check their recruitment status and print their examination slips. The State Police boss, Ayuba Elkanan said the Computer Based Test examinations printout will indicate the examination date, times, and designated centre for applicants. “In line with the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Usman Alkali Baba’s mission and vision for transparency and accountability in the exercise, the commissioner of Police Zamfara State Police Command assures the general public that the exercise will be conducted in the best tradition of transparency and accountability, and is purely free of charge and without any pecuniary obligation” he added. The commissioner who spoke through the command’s spokesman, SP Mohammed Shehu further congratulated the successful applicants and urged them to be law-abiding before, during and after the exercise.